Acting President Yemi Osinbajo has ordered military and intelligence agencies to rescue women recently abducted in Borno State by the Boko Haram.The acting president, in a statement yesterday by his spokesman, Laolu Akande, also directed security agencies to beef up security in and around the state.Osinbajo sympathised with families of the captives, condemned the abduction and described it as atrocious and cowardly act.